&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Enterprise Business Development Representative&lt;/strong&gt; plays a critical role in the growth of the company’s enterprise customer base. This role is responsible for identifying, qualifying, and developing new high-value business opportunities within large-scale organizations. He/she prospects into a target list of Enterprise accounts, with the aim of uncovering opportunities to sell Jamf products. He/she will leverage our Channel partners, as well as social media, webinars, events, phone and sales tools such as Groove, in order to build relationships with decision makers and advise on Jamf’s solutions to solve business challenges. The Enterprise BDR will collaborate with Marketing and one or more Key Account Manager(s) to identify target accounts, initiate contact with decision makers, and nurture prospects through early stages of the sales cycle.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
